      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "cli-runner: disable no-output watchdog when stdin is closed",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Disable the no-output watchdog for CLI backend spawns where `input` is provided\n- When input is provided, stdin is immediately closed after writing, so the process cannot be waiting for interactive input\n- The overall timeout (`timeoutMs`) still protects against runaway processes\n\n## Problem\n\nCLI backends like Claude Code get killed by the no-output watchdog when doing long-running silent work (e.g., research, translation). The watchdog assumes silence means \"waiting for user input,\" but stdin is already closed for these spawns.\n\n## Solution\n\nSkip setting `noOutputTimeoutMs` when `stdinPayload` is provided to `supervisor.spawn()`. The stdin-closed state means the watchdog's detection logic doesn't apply.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Existing no-output timer tests pass\n- [x] CLI runner tests pass (24/24)\n- [ ] Verify CLI backend with long silent work completes without being killed\n- [ ] Verify overall timeout still kills runaway processes",
